SimonSays – Simply Speak — ChangeLog
=========================================

Beta Releases
-------------

2026-07-31 Version 0.7
   - New features:
     * Board & category styles: the category window's look is now customizable through a CSS-like `property:value;` style cascade — a board-wide layer (background, separator color, a strip `caption`, board `title`/`credits`, text style, and defaults for all category/phrase buttons: colors, sizes as pixels or percentages, corner radius, border width, margin, icon position/size, font name/size/weight, text layout) plus per-category overrides (the category key's colors, which also flow to its phrase keys, and any phrase-button property). Unset properties fall back to the previous layer.
     * SPC communication boards: the style system was built to reproduce SPC/Fitzgerald color-coded boards — one `background` color per category paints the class key and all its phrase keys; a ready-to-import example ships in the spec (`docs/specs/board-style.spec.md`, Appendix A).
     * Styles travel with the board: the board layer is stored under the reserved `$$board` name and per-category styles as `$$` tokens, so exporting/importing `.ssc`/`.ssz` files carries the full look. Exporting a single category carries only that category's style. Category styles are edited in the existing edit dialog via a `::` suffix (`<icon>##<name>::background:#FFD966;`).
     * Smart label placement: a button's text is centered within the space left over by its icon (icon on top → caption centered in the band below it, the standard AAC symbol look; centered in the whole button when there is no icon). Explicit alignments such as `text-layout:top` still pin the text to an edge; `text-layout:smart` selects the centered default.
     * `icon-position:center` places the icon in the middle of a button and hides the text, for icon-only keys (an explicit `text-layout` keeps the text, drawn over the centered icon).
     * PNG and JPG icons: category and phrase icons now accept `.png` and `.jpg` image files in addition to `.ico` and emoji (e.g. `smile.png##Greetings`). PNG transparency is preserved, images keep their proportions on the button, and very large files are automatically reduced when loaded so they stay light and safe. Exported `.ssz` boards bundle the new image icons just like `.ico` files, and the in-app Help (`F1`) documents the new formats (English; other languages to follow).
   - Fixes and improvements:
     * Hardened registry loading: a hand-corrupted or non-numeric setting in `HKCU\SOFTWARE\SimonSays` (for example `Voice Volume`, `Voice Rate`, the category window size, `Zoom Factor`, the selected category, or the run counters) no longer crashes the app on launch — the affected value now falls back to its default.
     * More complete translations: the `Gaze / Dwell-click` window, the board-style-changed and delete-all-categories confirmations, and the import/export file dialogs are now translated in Spanish, Catalan, Valencian, Galician, French, German, Italian and Portuguese (they previously appeared in English in those languages). The Catalan tray `Feedback` entry, which mistakenly showed Spanish text, was also corrected. The remaining languages (Arabic, Chinese, Hebrew, Hindi, Japanese, Korean, Russian) still fall back to English for these strings and will follow.
   - Notes:
     * `$$`-prefixed category names are now reserved and rejected in the edit dialogs.
     * A board can carry a `caption` shown between the window's separators, and `title`/`credits` shown when the board is imported (crediting its author).
     * When text colors are not specified, readable black/white text is derived automatically from the styled background.
     * The in-app Help (`F1`) now documents the board/category style syntax, properties, and an SPC example (English; other languages to follow).
     * Older SimonSays versions importing a styled file show the style entries as harmless extra categories/phrases that can be deleted.
     * There is no style-editing UI yet: board styles arrive via import (or the registry). Importing a file that carries a board style asks before replacing an existing one (applied silently when none exists).

2026-06-04 Version 0.6
   - Focus on UI polish, stability, and bug fixes from the 0.5 release.
   - New features:
     * New `SSButton` class: custom owner-drawn Win32 button with rounded corners, per-state colors, icon/emoji rendering via Direct2D/DirectWrite, and flexible layout (icon position: left, right, top, bottom). Replaces all raw HWND buttons in `CategoryWindow` and `MainWindow`.
     * Icon/emoji support for categories and phrases: categories and phrases can now carry an icon field (emoji or `.ico` file), displayed on their corresponding buttons in the category window.
     * Emoji prefixes on built-in category names: all default phrase category names across every supported language now display a relevant emoji prefix for quicker visual scanning.
   - Fixes and improvements:
     * Fixed crash on SAPI/MCI shutdown: corrected COM apartment threading alignment and eliminated a heap-corruption race where SAPI async callbacks could fire after `Release()`. SAPI is now purged synchronously before the voice object is released.
     * Fixed thread-safety issue in `InterruptCurrentPlayback`: `m_pVoice->Speak` purge is now only called from the worker thread, preventing COM apartment violations when stop is triggered from the main thread.
     * Improved window restore on second-instance launch: the main window is now properly un-minimized (`SW_RESTORE`) instead of just made visible, and the `WM_COPYDATA` logic was simplified.
     * Refactored `CategoryWindow` layout into a centralized `LayoutCalcs()` method, reducing duplication and ensuring consistent positioning across all layout updates.
     * Delayed `CategoryWindow` display until after categories are populated to prevent an empty-window flash on startup.
     * Cached taskbar color and improved brush management in `CategoryWindow` to keep theming in sync with system color/theme changes.
     * Centralized edit control text reading in `MainWindow` via `ReadEditControlText`, making text handling in playback and append operations more robust.
     * Voice preview in the Settings dialog now runs on a background thread so the UI remains responsive during preview playback.
     * Static C runtime linkage (`/MT`): the binary now links the C runtime statically, removing the dependency on the MSVC redistributable DLL for a simpler deployment.
     * Installer now launches correctly the application after installation.
   - Notes:
     * Category and phrase icons are optional. Existing phrase sets without an icon field continue to work without modification.
     * The `SSButton` class requires Direct2D/DirectWrite for emoji rendering; these are available on all supported Windows versions.

2026-04-18 Version 0.5
   - Major update: threaded playback engine, MP3 support, audio ducking, and responsive stop/cancel.
   - Highlights:
     * New `PlaybackEngine`: audio playback and TTS run on a background worker thread so the UI remains responsive during long phrases or many segments.
     * MP3 playback support: `.mp3` files can now be embedded inline (in addition to `.wav`, `.mid`, `.midi`) using the `SOUND_NOTE_DELIMITER`.
     * Immediate stop/cancel capability: a global Stop action halts ongoing speech and inline sound playback (SAPI, PlaySound and MCI-backed MP3) without waiting for the current segment to finish.
     * Audio ducking: mute other applications and raise system master volume while speaking; both are restored automatically when playback finishes. Controlled via two independent Settings checkboxes (`Increase SimonSays volume when playing` and `Temporarily reduce other audio when playing`). Uses Windows Core Audio API (`IAudioSessionManager2`, `IAudioEndpointVolume`).
     * Stop previous playback: optional setting to automatically stop any ongoing playback when a new phrase is triggered. Controlled via the `Stop previous playback` setting.
     * Touch keyboard support: optional on-screen keyboard that opens when the input box receives focus, positioned near the main window. Uses `ITipInvocation` COM interface with `TabTip.exe` fallback. Controlled via the `Show touch keyboard` setting.
   - Fixes and improvements:
     * Significant UI responsiveness improvements when playing long text or sequences with multiple embedded sounds.
     * Resolved race conditions and rare crashes when triggering phrases rapidly or changing voice settings during playback.
     * Improved handling of unmatched delimiters and malformed inline file names.
     * Added "aww" and "censor" sounds to phrases and docs
   - Notes for users and integrators:
     * The playback behavior changed to asynchronous by design — if your workflow relied on synchronous blocking behaviour, use the provided Stop control to cancel playback or modify code to await the playback finished notification (`WM_PLAYBACK_STARTED` / `WM_PLAYBACK_FINISHED`).
     * Playback now posts `WM_PLAYBACK_STARTED` and `WM_PLAYBACK_FINISHED` to the main window to allow UI updates and external integration.
     * MP3 playback uses MCI; ensure that file paths are valid and accessible. Alias names are managed internally; avoid external MCI calls that reuse common aliases.
     * Voice selection and audio settings are still saved to registry and applied automatically; large changes to voice providers may require restarting the app in rare cases.
     * Audio ducking mutes other apps entirely (rather than reducing their volume) and sets the system master volume to maximum; if the application is terminated abnormally, other apps may remain muted and the system volume may stay at maximum until adjusted manually.
   - Known limitations:
     * Some very old or uncommon MP3 codecs may not play via the system MCI subsystem on all Windows installations.
     * The touch keyboard positioning relies on `TabTip.exe` availability; it may not appear on systems where the touch keyboard component is disabled or missing.


2026-03-24 Version 0.4
   - Major update with significant new features, improvements, and bug fixes.
   - New features:
     * Added support for user-defined custom categories and phrases directly through the UI.
     * Implemented import/export functionality for phrase sets with language metadata and conflict resolution (added ".ssc" file extension for "SimonSays Categories Backup").
     * Expanded bundled sound effects library and integrated them into the phrase picker.
     * Built-in help system with tooltips and a comprehensive user guide accessible from the category window.
   - Fixes:
     * Resolved several edge cases causing crashes when rapidly triggering phrases with certain voices or audio files.
     * Improved stability of the category window, especially after prolonged use or with large phrase sets.
     * Addressed various UI issues, including better handling of long translated strings and improved accessibility features.
     * Updated help documentation formatting and wording consistency in `HELP.md` and translated help files under `docs/help`.
   - Notes:
     * This release represents a significant step towards a more user-friendly and feature-rich experience. Users are encouraged to update to benefit from the new capabilities and improvements.

2026-02-14 Version 0.3.1
   - Hotfix release addressing critical stability issues and minor bugs from 0.3.
   - New features:
     * Added support for left-aligned bottom taskbars (previously only center-aligned bottom taskbars were fully supported).
   - Fixes:
     * Resolved a rare crash when rapidly triggering phrases with certain voices.
     * Fixed an issue where the category window could become unresponsive after prolonged use.
     * Corrected several UI mistranslations across supported languages.
   - Notes:
     * Recommended for all users of version 0.3 to ensure optimal performance and stability.
   
2026-02-02 Version 0.3
   - Beta release with enhanced stability, usability, and localization coverage.
   - New features:
     * Taskbar resilience: low-level mouse hook detects taskbar clicks and triggers Z-order recovery.
     * Faster Z-order polling when needed; stops automatically once restored to reduce CPU use.
     * Voice selection UI with language-specific voice filtering and safer fallbacks when voices are missing.
     * 12 new languages supported with localized default phrase sets.
     * Full localization of UI text in supported languages, including configuration labels.
     * Category window is resizable, remembers its size, and better fits translated strings.
   - Fixes:
     * Resolved issues with sound playback timing and overlapping audio; added throttling for rapid triggers.
     * Improved error handling for missing audio files and unsupported formats with clearer notifications.
     * UI enhancements for better accessibility and responsiveness (keyboard focus, high-contrast tweaks).
   - Notes:
     * Continued refinement of registry management for multi-user environments.
     * Current supported languages: Arabic, Basque, Catalan, Chinese (Simplified), English, French, Galician, German, Hebrew, Hindi, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese, Russian, Spanish, Valencian. More coming in minor updates.



Development Releases
--------------------
2025-11-30 Version 0.2
   - Feature-rich development build (alpha to early beta) focused on sound pipeline and phrase defaults.
   - New features:
     * Added Italian and Portuguese default phrase sets and Sounds categories.
     * Default phrase installation API: `RegistryManager::InstallDefaultPhrases()` (programmatic).
     * Play pipeline: editor text is parsed by the SOUND_NOTE_DELIMITER. Segments are played in order:
       - Plain text segments are spoken with SAPI (synchronous).
       - Delimited segments are treated as audio file names and played via `PlaySound` (synchronous).
     * Sound support for common audio files (.wav, .mid/.midi) and inline sound markers in the edit control.
     * Expanded `REGISTRY_SETUP.reg` with more categories and frequency-sorted phrases for multiple languages.
     * Category window layout and theming improvements (dark/light taskbar detection, rounded corners).
     * Compact taskbar UI tweaks: play button state, centered edit font, multiline edit support.
   - Fixes:
     * Robust handling of unmatched delimiters and trimming of segments before playback.
     * Safer registry read/write with fallbacks to English defaults.
     * Minor stability fixes for voice object lifecycle handling.
   - Notes:
     * Still in alpha/beta: expect incomplete voice-selection UI, partial localization of UI text, and no sync/import/export UX.
     * Registry changes are applied to HKCU only; importing system-wide settings requires elevation.

2025-11-13 Version 0.1
   - First release — proof of concept. (Alpha stage with basic functionality)
   - Features:
     * Taskbar-resident utility that converts typed text to speech using SAPI.
     * Quick-access categories and frequent phrases (multi-language registry-backed defaults).
     * Registry setup file (`REGISTRY_SETUP.reg`) with default phrase sets.
     * Basic language detection to pick phrase sets (English, Spanish, French, German, etc.).

2025-10-22 
   - Project initialization.
